  <text>
    <body>
      <ab type="lido:objectWorkType">Photograph</ab>
      <ab type="lido:event" subtype="creation">
        <date>1930-11-30</date>
      <persName role="Photographer"><surname>unknown</surname><ref type="context" target="info:fedora/context:siba.pn.unknown">unknown</ref></persName></ab>
      <ab type="lido:objectDescriptionSet">A line of cars crossing Galata Bridge. Pedestrians on the pavement are watching the scene. Letterings and flags are mounted on some of the cars. The first car that is fully visible in the line is equipped with an US flag on the enginehood and a plate on top that is lettered This is the parade you were waiting for' ('İşte beklediğiniz resmigeçit'), followed by a reference to 'Ford Transports' (Ford Nakliye'). On the very right, a porter is carrying a flat and round construction with textiles on top over his head. Wires, poles, and tracks are installed on the bridge. The cityscape in the background shows Galata neighbourhood of <ref target="http://gams.uni-graz.at/o:siba.glossar?mode=B9">Beyoğlu</ref> and <ref target="http://gams.uni-graz.at/o:siba.glossar?mode=G1">Galata Tower</ref>.</ab>
      <ab type="lido:objectDescriptionSet" subtype="comment">The picture was published on 1 December in Cumhuriyet newspaper along with a short article. The article states that the parade took place the day before and traces the route which led from <ref target="http://gams.uni-graz.at/o:siba.glossar?mode=T9">Tophane Ford fabrikası</ref> over the Galata Bridge through Fatih before turning back over the Galata Bridge to <ref target="http://gams.uni-graz.at/o:siba.glossar?mode=T2">Taksim</ref> Square, Şişli and Beşiktaş.</ab>
